gui_dim_foreground(25.10)                            gui_dim_foreground(25.10)

Name
       gui_dim_foreground - Dims the display area to the specified level

Syntax
       gui_dim_foreground

       [-help]

       -lightness_level {default medium dark}

       Dims  the display area to the specified level. Use this command to view
       selected and highlighted objects clearly against the dimmed foreground.
       This command is especially useful when you are debugging.

       The equivalent bindkey is F12.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each gui_dim_foreground parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man gui_dim_foreground.

       -lightness_level {default medium dark}
              Specifies the brightness level of the foreground in the  display
              area.

